analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: GMS Status: 39 (Defensive). Momentum pushed the score down from 41, signaling a risk-off regime. Macro Root: Rising DXY (Dollar strength/Liquidity) and widening HY spreads indicate tightening credit conditions. Risk/Reward: While VIX (Fear/Volatility) remains elevated at 20.6, key AI sector personnel shifts provide a potential niche catalyst. Conclusion: Maintain a defensive posture with higher cash allocations until the momentum vector shows a structural reversal toward accumulation.
